The magnitude of the electrostatic force between two point charges is directly proportional to the product of the magnitudes of the charges and inversely proportional to the square of the distance between them.  ```math
F = \frac{kQ_1Q_2}{r^2}
```

Electric field strength (E) is the force per unit charge: ```math
E = \frac{F}{q}
```  The units are N¬∑C‚Åª¬π.

